      <abstract>
        <p>A typical feature of Kindler Syndrome is skin fragility; this condition in currently
classified as a form of epidermolysis bullosa. We describe a rarely reported feature
of two cases, one sporadic and one familial; both patients noticed acquired
adermatoglyphia. The loss of dermatoglyphics could be an additional feature of this
syndrome.</p>
      </abstract>
